188.7	Arrested_Development_(TV_series)	Arrested Development (TV series)	Arrested Development is an American television sitcom created by Mitchell Hurwitz for the Fox Broadcasting Company. The show's storyline centers on the Bluth family, a formerly wealthy, habitually dysfunctional family, and is presented in a continuous format, incorporating hand-held camera work, narration, archival photos, and historical footage. Ron Howard is an executive producer and the uncredited narrator. Although set in Newport Beach, California, Arrested Development was primarily filmed around Culver City and Marina del Rey. Three seasons of the show were produced and aired between 2003 and 2006. On October 2, 2011, it was announced that the show will return in 2013 for a nine or ten episode mini-series that will lead up to a feature-length film. On November 18, 2011, it was confirmed that Netflix would exclusively license an unspecified number of new episodes for an early 2013 debut on its streaming video service.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e3/Arrested_Development.svg/250px-Arrested_Development.svg.png
